		PMON Targets
		PMON Targets

PMON supports any of LSI Logic's Evaluation boards as a Target.  Each
PMON target needs to be equipped with a set of suitably configured PMON
Proms.  This package currently builds for the following boards.

BDMR400x (4001/2/3) Evaluation Board

  »  Insert the four flash memories containing PMON in U8,
	U19, U29, and U40. Note that this board can be configured for
	big or little endian byte ordering (J1).
  »  Connect a serial cable from U28 to the 
	Host.

BDMR4101 (4101) Evaluation Board

  »  Insert the four flash memories containing PMON in U5,
	U6, U7, and U8. Note that this board can be configured for
	big or little endian byte ordering (J1).
  »  Connect a serial cable from J28 to the 
	Host.

BDMR4102 (4102) Evaluation Board

  »  Insert the EPROM containing PMON in U25.
  »  Connect a serial cable from J10 to the 
	Host.

Nitro (4010) Evaluation Board

  »  Insert the flash memory containing PMON in U18.
  »  Connect a serial cable from J18 to the 
	Host.

Nitro II (4011) Evaluation Board

  »  Insert the EPROM containing PMON in U4.
  »  Connect a serial cable from J19 to the 
	Host.

SDP1000 (64008) RevA Evaluation Board

  »  Insert the two flash memories containing PMON in U42 and U44.
  »  Connect a serial cable from CON9 to the 
	Host.

SDP1000 (64108) RevB Evaluation Board

  »  Insert the two flash memories containing PMON in U50 and U49.
  »  Connect a serial cable from port1 to the 
	Host.

ATMizer-2 RT Platform

  »  Build two PMON configuartions: one for the ATMizer-2 Host, and one
    for the ATMizer-2 Sar. Insert the two flash memories in the respective
    sockets.
  »  Connect two serial cables to the 
Host: one from the Host-board's tty0, and
one from the Sar-board's tty0.

